documentation.text:
Smart contract library of mathematical functions operating with signed
 64.64-bit fixed point numbers.  Signed 64.64-bit fixed point number is
 basically a simple fraction whose numerator is signed 128-bit integer and
 denominator is 2^64.  As long as denominator is always the same, there is no
 need to store it, thus in Solidity signed 64.64-bit fixed point numbers are
 represented by int128 type holding only the numerator.

div(int128,int128).notice: Calculate x / y rounding towards zero.  Revert on overflow or when y is zero.

divu(uint256,uint256).notice: Calculate x / y rounding towards zero, where x and y are unsigned 256-bit integer numbers.  Revert on overflow or when y is zero.

fromInt(int256).notice: Convert signed 256-bit integer number into signed 64.64-bit fixed point number.  Revert on overflow.

mul(int128,int128).notice: Calculate x * y rounding down.  Revert on overflow.

sqrt(int128).notice: Calculate sqrt (x) rounding down.  Revert if x < 0.

toInt(int128).notice: Convert signed 64.64 fixed point number into signed 64-bit integer number rounding down.

toUInt(int128).notice: Convert signed 64.64 fixed point number into unsigned 64-bit integer number rounding down.  Revert on underflow.

natspec.notice: Smart contract library of mathematical functions operating with signed 64.64-bit fixed point numbers.  Signed 64.64-bit fixed point number is basically a simple fraction whose numerator is signed 128-bit integer and denominator is 2^64.  As long as denominator is always the same, there is no need to store it, thus in Solidity signed 64.64-bit fixed point numbers are represented by int128 type holding only the numerator.
